<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefab60a6-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s308404"><num value="308404">§ 308404.</num><heading> Sunset</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This program shall expire on the date that is 7 years after the date of enactment of this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idefab60a7-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/115/104/s3/a">Pub. L. 115–104, § 3(a)</ref>, <date date="2018-01-08">Jan. 8, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/131/2261">131 Stat. 2261</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idefab60a8-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idefab60a9-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idefab60aa-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The date of enactment of this chapter, referred to in text, is the date of enactment of <ref href="/us/pl/115/104">Pub. L. 115–104</ref>, which was approved <date date="2018-01-08">Jan. 8, 2018</date>.</p>
</note>
